{{Quote|The last ''Mando'' who came in here wrecked the place. You're all the kriffing same, and I don't want you in here...|The [[Unidentified bartender (Paradise Cantina)|Paradise Cantina's bartender]]|<ref name="Sacrifice" />}}
The '''Paradise Cantina''' was a rough and unkempt [[Cantina/Legends|bar]] on [[Bador]], one of [[Kuat/Legends|Kuat's]] two [[Moon/Legends|moons]]. Located in a seedy neighborhood of [[Bunar]], the cantina bore numerous scars from [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of conflicts, and hosted an often dangerous clientele. In [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], the [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] by the name of [[Jaing Skirata]] killed the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime boss]] [[Cherit]] at the Paradise Cantina, following a prolonged [[Lightfight|shootout]]. Not long after, [[Mandalore (title)/Legends|''Mand'alor'']] [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] and [[Mirta Gev]] traveled to the cantina in search of Skirata. Despite an initial conflict with the [[Unidentified bartender (Paradise Cantina)|Paradise's bartender]], the two were able to acquire a lead on Skirata's whereabouts and soon departed.

==Description==
{{Quote|I'm offended that they don't respect cultural diversity.|[[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]], remarking upon the Paradise Cantina's sign that forbade helmets|<ref name="Sacrifice" />}}
The Paradise Cantina was a run down [[Cantina/Legends|bar]] located on [[Bador]],<ref name="Sacrifice" /> one of two [[Moon/Legends|moons]] of the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core World]] [[Kuat]],<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> in a seedy neighborhood of the [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Bunar]]. Situated five [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometers]] south of a large public [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]], the cantina was built with masonry construction, and possessed multiple doors. Over the bar's entrance was a sign that read "Welcome to the Paradise Cantina," followed by a warning that no [[Armor|helmets]] were allowed inside. By the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the [[Second Galactic Civil War]], the Paradise Cantina's outer facade had fallen into a state of scarred disrepair: [[Blaster/Legends|blasterfire]] had left burnt blisters in the paint on the doors, the walls were pocked from the impact of multiple [[Slugthrower/Legends|ballistic]] rounds, and an amount of [[Blood/Legends|blood]] had been left to pool and dry near the entrance.<ref name="Sacrifice" />

The inside of the cantina featured tile flooring, and accommodations for patrons to sit while enjoying their [[Alcohol/Legends|drinks]]. The air smelled of stale [[Ale/Legends|ale]], vomit, and [[Oil/Legends|oil]]. The Paradise Cantina possessed a long countertop bar, attended to by a [[Bartender/Legends|barkeep]], with shelves stocked with liquor and stacked glasses located behind it. Complimentary [[Foodstuff/Legends|snacks]] were offered in dishes at the bar, including [[Pickle/Legends|pickles]] that bore a physical resemblance to [[Eye/Legends|eyeballs]]; establishment policy required the purchase of a drink in order to partake of the bar snacks.<ref name="Sacrifice" />

==History==
{{Quote|So what were you after ''here?"<br />"''Recovering stolen data.''"<br />"''You mean people around here can read?|Boba Fett and [[Mirta Gev]]|<ref name="Sacrifice" />}}
Constructed in the [[Standard year/Legends|years]] prior to the outbreak of the Second [[The galaxy/Legends|Galactic]] Civil War, the Paradise Cantina saw numerous conflicts in and around the establishment throughout its existence. In [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]], the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Mirta Gev]] tracked stolen data she had been hired to recover to the Paradise Cantina. At the same time, the [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] [[Jaing Skirata]] came to the Paradise in order to confront the local [[Crime lord/Legends|crime boss]] [[Cherit]] over the trafficking of [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] [[Gender/Legends|women]] to [[Kuati/Legends|Kuati]] [[Noble/Legends|nobles]]. Anticipating violence, Gev departed before a prolonged and damaging [[Lightfight|shootout]] broke out that left Cherit [[Death/Legends|dead]]. Local [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|security forces]] investigated the cantina in the aftermath.<ref name="Sacrifice" />

[[Standard week/Legends|Weeks]] later, Gev led her [[Parent/Legends|grandfather]], the reigning [[Mandalore (title)/Legends|''Mand'alor'']] [[Boba Fett]], to the Paradise Cantina in search of Skirata. Upon entering, the two came into conflict with the Paradise's [[Unidentified bartender (Paradise Cantina)|Kuati bartender]], who resented the Mandalorian pair's appearance after the havoc Skirata previously wreaked. Though he attempted to retrieve an illegal, sawn-off [[Tenloss Syndicate/Legends|Tenloss]] [[DXR-6 disruptor rifle|disruptor rifle]] from behind the bar, Fett and Gev successfully [[Unarmed combat/Legends|subdued]] the bartender and persuaded him to give up what information he had on Skirata. The Paradise's bartender pointed the pair toward the [[Tekshar Falls Casino]] in [[Kuat City]], where the remnant of Cherit's gang resided. Fett and Gev subsequently left the cantina without further incident.<ref name="Sacrifice" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Paradise Cantina first appeared in the novel [[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice|''Sacrifice'']], the fifth entry in the multi-[[Author/Legends|author]] ''[[Star Wars: Legacy of the Force]]'' series, written by [[Karen Traviss]] and published [[May 29]], [[2007]].<ref name="Sacrifice" />

